jamesos
    ~ build             : contains the JamesOS hdd
    > dev               : development-related files, not part of source code
        > trash         : files that are no longer needed (but who knows...)
        - structure     : this file, explains the structure of the project
        - style         : style guidelines, still WIP
        - todo          : to do list
    > kernel            : all kernel files
        > devices                       : implementation files for device headers
            > keyboard                  : implementation files for the keyboard header
                - keyboard_scancode.c   : constructs keys from scancodes
                - keyboard.c            : manages key events
            > terminal                  : implementation file for the terminal header 
                - terminal.c            : terminal implementation
        > include                       : kernel-related header files
            > devices                   : headers for interacting with devices (keyboard and terminal)
                - keyboard.h
                - terminal.h
            > kernel                    : headers that only the kernel should use
                > system                : system-related headers
                    - exceptions.h      : exception handlers
                    - gdt.h             : initializing the GDT
                    - idt.h             : initializing the IDT
                    - memory.h          : memory-related typedefs and macros
                    - pmm.h             : PMM initialization and allocation functions
                    - vmm.h             : VMM initialization and mapping & paging functions
                - kcontrol.h            : execution control (kernel panic)
                - kdebug.h              : debugging utility functions (logging and breakpoints)
                - kinfo.h               : stivale information and logging to the screen
                - shell.h               : header for initializing the shell that is not actually a shell
                - stivale2.h
        > kernel                : kmain and implementations for the headers that only the kernel should use
            > shell             : implementation files for the shell
            > system            : implementation files for the system headers
                > exceptions
                > gdt
                > idt
                > memory
            - kcontrol.c
            - kdebug.c
            - kinfo.c
            - kmain.c
    > libc              : libc implementation and headers (this is actually libk i guess)
    > limine            : limine source code and build
